Heat grill. Shape ground beef into 4 patties; season with salt and pepper. Place burgers on grill. Cover and cook over medium heat 10 to 11 minutes, turning once, or until no longer pink in center and juice is clear (160 degrees F. for burgers). Meanwhile, warm pita as package directs. Toss remaining ingredients; season with salt and pepper. Place burgers on pitas; top with vegetables. Fold burger in pita to eat.